<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7116> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7116" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 153. Treated as two persons, father and son, in both RE and MRR (1.413, 426, 447, 452, and Index, 2.530), he should be treated as one, since the junior and the senior offices attributed to the two can reasonably be held within the period of one career (Badian, Studies 248; Malcovati in ORF(2) 104; Sumner, Orators 40). Note that T. P. Wiseman, though without full proof that the Via Annia from Bononia through Patavium and Altinum to Aquileia precedes the building of the Via Postumia from Genua to Aquileia in 148, is inclined to attribute it to the consul of 153 rather than, with Degrassi, to T. Annius Rufus, Cos. 128, Pr. by 131 (PBSR 32, 1964, 21-37; 37, 1969, 82-91). See below, on T. Annius Rufus (78). Cos. 128.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2901> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2901" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Brut. 79; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 124, 464f. ([- - - -]n. Nobilior, T. Annius T. [- - - -]); Chr. 354 (Nobiliore et Fuso); Fast. Hyd. (Nobiliore et Lausco), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Fulvius, Fast. Ant., Degrassi 160f. (Q. Fulvi. N[- - - -]). Fulvius received the command against the Celtiberi in Hither Spain and suffered serious reverses (App. Ib. 45-47; cf. Polyb. 35.4.2). Beginning this year Consuls entered office on January (Cassiod.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2874> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2874" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest year under the Lex Villia." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2725> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2725" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "To add new colonists to Aquileia (Liv. 43.17.1)." .
